Here is how this repo lines up **Firebase (Google)** with **local dev**:

### Two supported dev shapes

**1. No Firebase in `.env` (minimal local stack)**  
If you leave the `VITE_FIREBASE_*` variables empty, the client is **not** using Firebase. Sign-in on `/login` tells you to use a **dev bearer token** instead (from `npm run dev:local-auth` → `/dev/token`, or `VITE_DEV_BEARER_TOKEN`). The API uses **`JWT_*` pointing at that local JWKS** (see `.env.example`). That path avoids creating any Firebase/GCP project.

**2. Firebase configured (real Google sign-in in dev)**  
You add the Web app keys from **Firebase Console → Project settings** into `.env` (documented in `.env.example`). The app uses **Google sign-in via Firebase Auth** (`signInWithPopup`). After sign-in, the web client prefers the **Firebase ID token** for API calls when the Firebase provider is registered:

```86:98:c:\Users\Ken Levy\OneDrive\Documents\Business\Ohana\Memories\apps\web\src\lib\api.ts
async function resolveBearerToken(): Promise<string | null> {
  if (firebaseIdTokenProvider) {
    try {
      const fromFirebase = normalizeToken(await firebaseIdTokenProvider());
      if (fromFirebase) {
        return fromFirebase;
      }
    } catch {
      /* fall through to dev token */
    }
  }
  return getDevBearerToken();
}
```

For that to work end-to-end, the **API must validate Firebase-issued JWTs**, not only the local-auth issuer. `.env.example` spells out the usual Firebase JWKS/issuer/audience pattern (`securetoken.google.com`, Google’s JWKS URL, audience = project id).

### What “Firebase is a Google product” implies in practice

- You typically use a **separate Firebase project for dev/staging** (still free-tier capable for Auth) so prod keys and rules stay isolated.  
- **Authorized domains** in Firebase (e.g. `localhost`) matter for the popup flow.  
- It does **not** force you to run everything on GCP for daily coding: either skip Firebase and use **local JWT**, or point both web and API at a **small dev Firebase project**.

So: **dev login is either “paste local JWT” or “configure a dev Firebase project + align API `JWT_*` with Firebase”—both are intentional; Firebase being on Google’s stack mostly means you choose a dev Firebase project when you want real Google sign-in locally.**

